                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="27624" author="yozh" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2007 05:36:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just created dup: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-4104&quot; title=&quot;JdbcDaoSupport.setJdbcTemplate() should accept JdbcOperations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-4104&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-4104&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. My reason is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have reflective proxy of JdbcTemplate that measures query execution times. Such proxy does not extend JdbcTemplate, but rather implement JdbcOperations. So I cannot inject this proxy into JdbcDaoSupport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27625" author="yozh" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2007 05:41:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To make change backward compatible:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add method setJdbcOperations()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add method getJdbcOperations()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;change jdbcTemplate field type to JdbcOperations (and rename to jdbcOperations)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getJdbcTemplate() should cast field jdbcOperations value to JdbcTemplate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="27705" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2007 22:47:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would argue that you shouldn&apos;t be using JdbcDaoSupport in the first place in such a case. Why not simply include a JdbcOperations field in your DAO class, with a corresponding constructor or setter? This is significantly nicer and you&apos;re not losing any relevant conveniences either...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main purpose of JdbcDaoSupport is to automatically build a JdbcTemplate for an injected DataSource. If you&apos;re injecting a JdbcTemplate directly (no matter whether raw or proxied), you&apos;re not really getting much benefit from JdbcDaoSupport in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27995" author="skaffman" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2007 18:07:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yup, that&apos;s fair comment.  I withdraw the request.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="27999" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2007 20:14:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, closing this issue then... I guess we should explicitly mention the non-JdbcDaoSupport option in the reference doc as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
